title.narrative: National partners have enhanced capacity to extend access to preschool, basic and post-basic education to the most vulnerablechildren.

description.narrative: Preschool education extension was supported through capacity building and decentralized planning, resulting an increase of 16 percent (72) percent of enrolment rate nationwide. Inclusive education policy extension was supported within 700 Primary schools. Out of school children programs enabled tracking 18,941 children and opening of 28 second chance schools nationwide | Status:Met | As-of Date:13/01/2022
